BLUETONGUE, BOVINE, OVINE - ISRAEL (05): (HAZAFON), BTV-5 FIRST REPORT, OIE
***************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Tue 10 Nov 2009
Source: OIE, WAHID interface [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=8635>


Bluetongue in Israel
--------------------
Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Start date: 28 Aug 2009
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 09 Nov 2009
Report date: 10 Nov 2009
Date submitted to OIE: 10 Nov 2009
Reason for notification: New strain of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: 5
Nature of diagnosis: Suspicion, Clinical, Laboratory (basic),
Laboratory (advanced), Necropsy
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1: Kanaf, Golan, Hazafon
Date of start of the outbreak: 28 Aug 2009
Epidemiological unit : Village
Affected animals
Species/ Susceptible/ Cases/ Deaths/ Destroyed Slaughtered
Sheep/ 50/ 8/ 6/ 0 /0
Affected population: The affected animals showed swollen heads

Outbreak 2: Bet Hillel, Tsefat, Hazafon
Date of start of the outbreak: 09 Oct 2009
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals
Species/ Susceptible/ Cases/ Deaths/ Destroyed/ Slaughtered
Cattle/50/20/1/0/0
Affected Population: Milk yield decrease and udder edema. Muscular
necrosis in one cow.
Epidemiological comments: This is a strain which had never been
diagnosed in Israel. The 2 outbreaks occurred in the north of the
country. The serotyping was done in the Pirbright laboratories.

Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Vectors

Control measures
Measures applied: Control of arthropods; screening; no vaccination
[see commentary]; no treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results
1. Laboratory name and type: Virology Laboratory, Kimron Veterinary
Institute (National laboratory)
Species/ Test/ Test date/ Result
Cattle/ polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 09 Nov 2009/ Positive.
Sheep/ polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 09 Nov 2009/ Positive.

2. Laboratory name and type: Pirbright Laboratory (OIE's Reference Laboratory)
Tests and results
Species/ Test/ Test date/ Result
Cattle/ polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 09 Nov 2009/ Positive
Sheep/ polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 09 Nov 2009/ Positive

